Industrialization has had a profound impact on the environment, both positive and negative. On the one hand, the advent of machinery and technology has increased efficiency and productivity, leading to economic growth. On the other hand, industrial activities have contributed to air and water pollution, deforestation, and the depletion of natural resources. In particular, the burning of fossil fuels for energy has been a major source of greenhouse gas emissions, which in turn contribute to global warming. As industrialization continues to spread globally, finding a balance between economic development and environmental protection remains a critical challenge for policymakers.